properties.value: A User Plane(UP)/Payload Processor(PP) Virtual Service Forwarder Provides virtual EPG applicationUser Plane capabilities for 2G,3G,LTE,WiFi, and NR (5G radio) configured as with an external SMF. VSFO can also provide virtual EPG application aware load balancing (ingress) and forwarding (egress). It provides Layer 2 and Layer 3 data forwarding.

428a6691-cb1f-4382-95e3-603643a6aebd.476.description: Human readable description of the VDU
428a6691-cb1f-4382-95e3-603643a6aebd.476.name: description
428a6691-cb1f-4382-95e3-603643a6aebd.476.value: A Control Plane (cp) Virtual Service Forwarder (VSFO) Provides virtual EPG application Control Plane capabilities for 2G,3G,LTE and WiFi, Control Plane VSFOs can be configured with external IP interfaces for ingress and egress user packet forwarding, same as User Plane VSFO. However, Control Plane VSFOs must not handle User Plane traffic because of capacity impact. Therefore, Ericsson does not recommend configuring Control Plane VSFOs for user packet forwarding.

428a6691-cb1f-4382-95e3-603643a6aebd.476.description: It indicates whether the order of the virtual_storage requirements is used as the boot index (the first requirement represents the lowest index and defines highest boot priority).
